```

## How it meets the spec

- **Login required** — Flask-Login guards every inventory route; passwords are hashed (`werkzeug.security`). A default `admin` / `admin` user is seeded on first run.
- **Add items** — name, SKU (unique), quantity, location, plus a per-item low-stock threshold. Server-side validation with friendly flash errors and duplicate-SKU handling.
- **Adjust quantities** — one-click +/− buttons (`/adjust/<id>`), clamped so quantity never goes below 0.
- **Search** — single box matching name, SKU, or location.
- **Low-stock highlight** — rows at/below threshold get an amber highlight + "Low" badge, with a running count badge in the header.
- **SQLite** — `inventory.db` is created automatically on first launch; no manual DB setup.
- **Port 5047** — `app.run(..., port=5047)` and documented in the README.

## Run it

```powershell
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py
```

Then open <http://127.0.0.1:5047> and log in with `admin` / `admin`.

